==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crummy
<hw>Crum"my</hw> <pr>(kr⟦ucr⟧m"m⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Full of crumb or crumbs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Soft, as the crumb of bread is; not
crusty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>of very poor quality.</def>
<mark>[informal]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bum, cheap, cheesy, chintzy, crummy, punk, sleazy,
tinny.</syn>
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crump</ent>⟦br⟧
